<item>
            <title>[FLUME-2886] Optional Channels can cause OOMs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-2886</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an optional channel is full, the queue backing the executor that is asynchronously submitting the events to the channel can grow indefinitely in size leading to a huge number of events on the heap and causing OOMs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
